BOMBERMAN-DOM:
    Structure:
        BOMBERMAN-DOM/
        │ 
        ├── doc/
        │   ├── AUDIT.md
        │   └── subject.md
        ├── src/
        │   ├── core/
        │   │   ├── chat.js       // contient les fonctions de gestion du chat
        │   │   ├── core.js       // contient les fonctions de gestion du jeux (start, stop, pause, resume)
        │   │   ├── game.js       // contient les fonctions de gestion du jeux
        │   │   ├── map.js        // contient les fonctions de génération de la map les bricks et les bonus
        │   │   ├── player.js     // contient les fonctions de déplacement (peut etre)
        │   │   ├── templates.js  // associe tous les ui du jeux
        │   │   └── utils
        │   │       └── helpers.js 
        │   ├── server/
        │   │   ├── server.go // s'il y'a du go 
        |   |   └── main.go
        |   └── assets/
        ├── index.html
        ├── README.md
        └── task.todo
    Require:
        Restrictions:
            ☐ Do not use Canvas, Web-GL, or other frameworks.
            ☐ Use the custom framework from the mini-framework project.
        Chat:
            ☐ Implement a chat feature for player communication using WebSockets.
        Players:
            ☐ Support 2 - 4 players.
            ☐ Each player starts with 3 lives.
        Map:
            ☐ Create a fixed map visible to all players.
            ☐ Include indestructible walls and destructible blocks.
            ☐ Place walls in fixed positions.
            ☐ Generate blocks randomly on the map.
            ☐ Ensure starting positions are safe from immediate bomb explosions.
            ☐ Place players in the corners at the start.
        Power-ups:
            ☐ Implement power-ups that appear randomly when blocks are destroyed:
                ☐ Bombs: Increase the number of bombs a player can drop.
                ☐ Flames: Increase the explosion range by 1 block.
                ☐ Speed: Increase movement speed.
        User Interface:
            ☐ Create a page for entering a nickname.
            ☐ Create a waiting page with a player counter.
            ☐ Increment player counter when a new player joins.
            ☐ Start a 10-second timer if more than 2 players join and the count doesn't reach 4 within 20 seconds.
            ☐ Start the game after the 10-second timer if 4 players join within 20 seconds.
    Bonus:
        Game Modes:
            ☐ Develop an AI for Solo + Co-Op mode.
            ☐ Implement a 2v2 Team mode.
        Additional Power-ups:
            ☐ Bomb Push: Ability to throw a bomb after placing
            ☐ Bomb Pass: Ability to
            ☐ Block Pass: Ability to
            ☐ Detonator: Ability to
            ☐ 1 Up: Grants an extra life.
            ☐ Drop power-ups upon player death.
        After Death Interaction:
            ☐ Implement ghost mode for dead players.
            ☐ Allow ghosts to resurrect other players by touching them.
            ☐ Ensure ghosts die permanently if caught in a bomb explosion.
    AUDIT:
        ☐ Verify game runs smoothly at 60fps.
        ☐ Test chat functionality.
        ☐ Ensure power-ups work as intended.
        ☐ Test different player configurations (2-4 players).
        ☐ Verify safety of starting positions.
        ☐ Ensure proper player elimination and game ending.
        ☐ confirm that there are at least 3 types of power ups

        //legende
        ☐ ctrl + Enter (initiliser une tâche)
        ☐ @started(24-05-25 13:45) ctrl + Enter / alt + s (pour demarrer une tâche)
        ✔ @done(24-05-25 13:46) alt + D (pour terminer une tâche)
        ✘ @cancelled(24-05-25 13:47) (pour annuler une tâche)